data.chText: 身体的机能 / 变化 / 需要

data.enText: by moving the whole of sb's body; by force

data.chText: 爆炸的力量把我们震落在地上。
data.enText: The force of the blast hurled us bodily to the ground.

data.chText: 他把她整个人举到空中。
data.enText: He lifted her bodily into the air.

data.chText: 整个纪念碑被迁到了新的地点。
data.enText: The monument was moved bodily to a new site.

tr: having or relating to a physical material body
affecting or characteristic of the body as opposed to the mind or spirit
example: a somatic symptom or somatic illness

tr: of or relating to or belonging to the body

example: he was translated bodily to heaven

value.def: Your bodily needs and functions are the needs and functions of your body.

example.tran: 对人体自然生理功能的描述

example.ex: There's more to eating than just bodily needs.
example.tran: 饮食不仅仅是出于身体的需要。

value.def: You use bodily to indicate that an action involves the whole of someone's body.

example.ex: I was hurled bodily to the deck.
example.tran: 我整个人都被摔到了甲板上。
